<br>
It is an extremely difficult things to do solo kill SG or HG at 34.  Some would say it is a big waste of time (I'd agree in a sense).  I tried it a few times just for fun.  It is definately NOT worth it if you are trying this for any reason other then, &quot;I feel like doing something very risky and nearly impossible today.&quot;<br>
<br>
- You pet will die so very FAST so you will need to chain at least 1 or more.<br>
<br>
- If you use pure &quot;Chain casting pets&quot;, you almost certainly run out of mana before you kill Giant.<br>
<br>
- If you Nuke &amp; Chain pets combo, you might be able to take the very lowest level Giant, but I'd say 90% of the time you will go OOM and die if the giant resists some nukes (and it probably will).  I am serious about the 90% too.<br>
<br>
- Overburn pet kiting with SoW will seem to work until Giant turns on pet and kills it in like 15 to 20 seconds.  If you get lucky, or are a good kiter and aggro control freak, have lots of mana, and Clarity/mana regen, you might pull this off by then tossing a few pets back at it -and- nuking when you can with Cinder.<br>
<br>
So...<br>
<br>
At 39 - with focused Earth Pet, I was able to take out 3 of every 4 or so HG or SG.   I'd pull with 2 or 3 Cinder Bolts to a focused Earth pet, run around pet till root stuck, and more Cinder Bolts till dead.  Other methods were much less reliable.<br>
<br>
And, as other posters said, the 44 pet can almost solo SG or HG, and ANY 49 pet can, even Fire, who usually can solo two at once even (lol).<br>
<br>
I'd suggest you wait till 39 at minimum.   Partner with a Necro, Druid, another Mage, Shaman for SG/HG at 34. <p><b>Seek Pyremaker</b><br>
